page.title: 10WILDFLOWERS AROUND FARLEY
page.content: In the woodland around Farley many wildflowers grow.In Farley Copse the bluebells grow abundantly in spring. Also there are many primroses and wood anemones. Later on Hound Wood is carpeted with Lily-of-the-Valley. Many interesting and rare orchids grow around Farley as well as the more usual wildflowers. One day in July 1985 we had a walk through Blackmoor Copse. Here are some of the flowers we saw:cow parsley, dock, nettles, cranesbill, vetch, blackberries, deadly nightshade, periwinkle, buttercups, clover, dandelions, daisy, dog rose, shepherd's purse, borrage, birds eyes, creeping Jenny, primrose, honeysuckle, moss, speedwell, wild strawberry, spotted orchid and butterfly orchid.
